hrough reading this whole thread, and go from aback to confused to chuckling to proud to...........<br>
<br>
I haven't been playing this game forever, started 4/2001, made first bard in 7/2001, parked him at 54th and made a new one in 2/2002, and no stopping from then. <br>
I will say: <br>
<br>
In Everquest I am a Bard.<br>
<br>
There ain't any other class that is as fun or offers as many options. Period.<br>
<br>
Ya ever talk to the wizzie that got invited to a dungeon crawl, not so he could nuke, but because the group needed an evaccer and no druid was available? Or the ranger that came along because there was no rogue LFG... <br>
<br>
For every situation: mob/zone/ect. there is an ideal group/raid setup. With this group you can do the mob with the least people, get the most experience in a certain time, and so on. Then there is who you actually find to come along, and in many cases it doesn't look like that ideal ya thought of. Guess what, whatever is missing, stick a bard there and the group will thrive. Thats why I like this class. (that includes the evaccer... ya won't need it with the bard there)<br>
<br>
Personally I don't really like raiding, and I would bet that there are a few other people playing this game that think the same thing. It's a necessary part of the high end game if you want cool toys but I am glad that I don't log in each day to guildchat saying &quot;Get to ************ right away, we gotta kill this or it will push our raid schedule back 4 days and 7 hours!&quot;<br>
<br>
So, to add to the reason why there maybe aren't eleventeen bards on the raiding guild's rosters... maybe they don't want to be there. Like Meiyu said, it takes a certain mindset.<br>
<br>
Anyway, on to the next topic. Bards are underpowered. <br>
<br>
/em laughs his tail off <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Granted I just got myself kilt fighting the first nak spawn in chardok the other day before my partner got there... /rude dungeons... but there ain't any other class on the server that can solo dark blue con mobs in the mid 50s nonstop for hours if they feel like it. OR do the same for their group. I never hear &quot;OOM, med break&quot;.... we hear &quot;80M gtg&quot; in more groups than any other class, guaranteed.<br>
<br>
Finally, the gear issue. I am just now at level 57 starting to get some decent toys, took off the last piece of lambent at 56, still wearing some ry`gorr now, all 4 melee stats just barely over 100, charisma just high enough that mezes don't get resisted too much, still using 3 storebought instruments, and i have to say:<br>
<br>
Equipment Doesn't Matter in how useful I am.<br>
<br>
Ok, this post is getting too long, I'm done for now.<br>
<br>
Have fun playing everyone, thats what the game is about anyway. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Ciryn<br>
57 Kittybard of Indicium<br>
